I said I don't want to do this.

276
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:47,020
-Why not?
-Just because.

277
00:22:48,020 --> 00:22:49,150
I'm not doing it.

278
00:22:49,230 --> 00:22:50,820
Why?

279
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:53,200
Why do you not want to do this?

280
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:55,070
You've been doing well
with the counseling.

281
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,910
You need to face this to get better.

282
00:22:56,990 --> 00:23:00,120
Will you keep living as a doctor
who can't operate?

283
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:03,960
Maybe later.

284
00:23:04,500 --> 00:23:05,790
I'll do it some other time.

285
00:23:05,870 --> 00:23:07,130
When would it be?

286
00:23:07,580 --> 00:23:10,050
It's about time
to stop torturing yourself.

287
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:21,260
-Here.
-Thanks.

288
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:24,890
Now you look like Cha Yu-ri.

289
00:23:27,980 --> 00:23:29,020
Yu-ri.

290
00:23:29,650 --> 00:23:30,480
Yes?

291
00:23:30,570 --> 00:23:32,280
For the past five years,

292
00:23:34,650 --> 00:23:37,360
were you around me as well?

293
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:41,910
Sure. I stuck around you all the time.

294
00:23:43,540 --> 00:23:47,330
Even I forgot my birthday,
but you remembered it every year.

295
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,840
Maybe I was struggling not to forget you.

296
00:23:53,630 --> 00:23:55,220
I guess that's why.

297
00:23:56,930 --> 00:23:58,050
After you left,

298
00:23:59,090 --> 00:24:00,850
it didn't really hit me at first.

299
00:24:01,850 --> 00:24:03,310
When I studied abroad,

300
00:24:03,390 --> 00:24:05,810
we didn't see each other for about a year.

301
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:07,940
It was like that.

302
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:11,690
I felt like you were just away
for a little bit.

303
00:24:14,070 --> 00:24:19,070
And once I realized that I would
never be able to see you again,

304
00:24:20,410 --> 00:24:22,330
I couldn't even eat.

305
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:24,660
I just cried my eyes out.

306
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:28,670
But after a little while,

307
00:24:29,620 --> 00:24:31,420
I felt hungry again.

308
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:35,010
So I started to eat,

309
00:24:35,380 --> 00:24:36,970
take care of Ha-jun,

310
00:24:37,090 --> 00:24:38,180
and work.

311
00:24:42,140 --> 00:24:43,430
And one day,

312
00:24:46,730 --> 00:24:47,810
I realized that

313
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:50,400
I was forgetting about you.

314
00:24:53,110 --> 00:24:54,690
I just celebrated your birthdays

315
00:24:55,690 --> 00:24:57,570
because I wanted to cling on to you.

316
00:24:58,610 --> 00:25:00,320
Because I was sorry for you.

317
00:25:03,530 --> 00:25:04,870
And you knew it, right?

318
00:25:05,700 --> 00:25:06,910
Of course, I did.

319
00:25:07,540 --> 00:25:10,290
Actually I was sad
that you were forgetting about me.

320
00:25:12,540 --> 00:25:13,540
But

321
00:25:15,750 --> 00:25:19,090
I was afraid if I wouldn't be forgotten.

322
00:25:22,050 --> 00:25:25,260
Watching people
have hard times because of me,

323
00:25:26,310 --> 00:25:28,100
was real hell.

324
00:25:29,810 --> 00:25:30,640
Gang-hwa?

325
00:25:35,190 --> 00:25:36,780
So you knew it too.

326
00:25:37,860 --> 00:25:39,320
That Gang-hwa has a problem.

327
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:42,740
I do. I was around him all the time.

328
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,330
He recently received a probation.

329
00:25:46,410 --> 00:25:48,080
I found out about it later on though.

330
00:25:51,830 --> 00:25:53,710
That's what I did to him.

331
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:56,210
I broke his heart.

332
00:25:56,290 --> 00:25:58,090
It's not your fault.

333
00:25:58,460 --> 00:26:00,510
Isn't it like you died
because you wanted to.

334
00:26:02,180 --> 00:26:03,890
But it was my choice.

335
00:26:06,430 --> 00:26:08,850
I just made him feel guilty.

336
00:26:28,330 --> 00:26:31,410
Where did she go leaving me alone?

337
00:26:34,330 --> 00:26:35,330
Oh, right.

338
00:26:37,090 --> 00:26:37,920
That's right.

339
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:46,260
SUPERNATURAL POWERS
SHAMAN MS. MI-DONG

340
00:26:46,850 --> 00:26:49,640
SEO BONG-YEON

341
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:05,320
I know you're a stone-hearted human,

342
00:27:05,910 --> 00:27:10,240
but how could you send them up
just like that?

343
00:27:10,330 --> 00:27:11,790
My point.

344
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:14,290
I didn't even get to say goodbye. Damn it.

345
00:27:20,050 --> 00:27:21,590
You guys are not human.

346
00:27:23,510 --> 00:27:24,880
To Guk-bong...

347
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:27,180
I mean, to people,

348
00:27:27,430 --> 00:27:29,800
you guys are just demons
who should be sent up.

349
00:27:29,890 --> 00:27:31,600
How could you say something so harsh?

350
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:32,890
I know.

351
00:27:32,970 --> 00:27:35,890
So if you don't want to get caught
and sent up all of a sudden like them,

352
00:27:36,100 --> 00:27:37,850
stop avoiding Guk-bong

353
00:27:38,230 --> 00:27:42,360
and get over your regrets in this world.

354
00:27:45,950 --> 00:27:47,360
This is really frustrating.

355
00:27:55,040 --> 00:27:56,160
Hello?

356
00:27:56,250 --> 00:27:57,540
Hello, ma'am.

357
00:27:58,210 --> 00:27:59,790
Do you make domiciliary visits?

358
00:28:00,130 --> 00:28:01,130
What?

359
00:28:07,180 --> 00:28:09,720
Min-jeong. Believe it or not,

360
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:11,600
it's true.

361
00:28:29,280 --> 00:28:30,450
What are you doing?

362
00:28:31,410 --> 00:28:32,580
Get off, Yu-ri.

363
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:36,830
You said we'd hang out at my place.

364
00:28:37,410 --> 00:28:38,920
We will drink. So I can't drive.

365
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:40,000
Let's walk.

366
00:28:44,300 --> 00:28:46,300
I'm hungry. Let's go.

367
00:29:00,310 --> 00:29:01,600
-I'm so hungry.
-Me too.

368
00:29:01,690 --> 00:29:03,690
-I shouted too much.
-I know.

369
00:29:03,770 --> 00:29:06,740
I couldn't help it
because you drove so fast.

370
00:29:17,580 --> 00:29:18,580
-Is it here?
-Yes.

371
00:29:18,660 --> 00:29:19,660
It's for us.

372
00:29:19,830 --> 00:29:21,620
-It just came right on time.
-I know.

373
00:29:22,460 --> 00:29:23,710
-Please enjoy.
-Thank you.

374
00:29:23,790 --> 00:29:25,300
It's pork belly meat.

375
00:29:25,380 --> 00:29:27,800
-Let's go.
-Mom, Yu-ri and Hyeon-jeong are here.

376
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:30,050
Gosh, I can't wait.

377
00:29:30,260 --> 00:29:33,640
-Let's eat.
-It must be really good.

378
00:29:34,890 --> 00:29:36,430
Hello, Ms. Jeon.

379
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:49,280
CHA MU-PUNG, JEON EUN-SUK,
CHA YU-RI, CHA YEON-JI

380
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:29,150
-It looks delicious.
-It's warm.

381
00:30:29,230 --> 00:30:30,240
My goodness.

382
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:32,400
-I'm hungry.
-It looks great.

383
00:30:32,490 --> 00:30:35,370
Here's a cold beer for you.

384
00:30:35,450 --> 00:30:37,200
Yeon-ji, you're the best.

385
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:38,740
We have five drinkers here.

386
00:30:38,830 --> 00:30:40,660
This is far from enough.

387
00:30:40,830 --> 00:30:42,540
I don't drink beer.

388
00:30:42,620 --> 00:30:43,580
I like soju.

389
00:30:43,790 --> 00:30:47,040
I knew it. You're so my type.

390
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,800
Mom, I'll get you soju.

391
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:51,170
Here, Dad.

392
00:30:51,260 --> 00:30:52,590
-My daughter is the best.
-Gosh.

393
00:30:52,670 --> 00:30:53,720
It's good, isn't it?

394
00:30:54,970 --> 00:30:57,350
-This is nice.
-Dad, please open this for me.

395
00:30:57,430 --> 00:30:58,810
Give me that.

396
00:30:58,890 --> 00:31:00,350
All right.

397
00:31:02,310 --> 00:31:03,520
It's open.

398
00:31:04,190 --> 00:31:06,400
It flew away like this.

399
00:31:06,980 --> 00:31:08,400
Let's drink.

400
00:31:08,480 --> 00:31:10,480
Here. Have some of this.

401
00:31:10,570 --> 00:31:12,280
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

402
00:31:12,360 --> 00:31:14,240
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

403
00:31:18,120 --> 00:31:19,740
It tastes so good.

404
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:25,920
So we're all together with Hyeon-jeong.

405
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,790
It's been so long since we did this.

406
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:29,040
I know.

407
00:31:29,130 --> 00:31:31,960
I've been too busy
working and raising my kid.

408
00:31:32,460 --> 00:31:34,840
She was just afraid
she would remind us of Yu-ri,

409
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:36,890
so she was being thoughtful.

410
00:31:37,760 --> 00:31:39,350
Do you think I don't know that?

411
00:31:41,470 --> 00:31:43,060
I had no idea

412
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:46,770
this day would come again.

413
00:31:46,850 --> 00:31:49,110
What are you doing, Dad? This isn't right.

414
00:31:49,190 --> 00:31:52,480
She's right. Why are you being so silly?

415
00:31:52,570 --> 00:31:53,860
Okay. I get it.

416
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:55,780
-I'm done. It's over.
-It's over.

417
00:31:56,110 --> 00:31:58,950
-Mr. Cha, please stop.
-What's over?

418
00:31:59,030 --> 00:32:01,870
It's nothing.
Your dad is just being silly again.

419
00:32:01,950 --> 00:32:03,910
Do you say things like that?

420
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:05,080
Sure.

421
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,290
She says all kinds of stuff.

422
00:32:06,370 --> 00:32:08,420
-Gosh, Dad.
-Stop it.

423
00:32:10,590 --> 00:32:12,130
-It tastes good.
-So

424
00:32:12,670 --> 00:32:14,090
did you guys have fun?

425
00:32:14,170 --> 00:32:15,420
Yes. We had a lot of fun.

426
00:32:15,510 --> 00:32:18,800
Hyeon-jeong's driving has improved a lot.
She was too afraid to run at 50km before.

427
00:32:18,890 --> 00:32:20,180
Hey, that was a long time ago.

428
00:32:20,260 --> 00:32:24,180
That's not true.
I was a novice driver back then.

429
00:32:24,270 --> 00:32:26,600
Still, 50km is too slow.

430
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:29,480
Here, Yu-ri. Try this.

431
00:32:29,560 --> 00:32:31,810
You seem to have only one daughter.

432
00:32:31,900 --> 00:32:34,150
You're my son. All right.

433
00:32:34,230 --> 00:32:36,990
I didn't know I was a son.

434
00:32:37,070 --> 00:32:40,780
All right. I should give this to my son.

435
00:32:40,870 --> 00:32:43,120
Here. Good.

436
00:32:43,410 --> 00:32:44,950
Why don't we take a picture together?

437
00:32:45,040 --> 00:32:46,660
-Good.
-Let's do that.

438
00:32:46,750 --> 00:32:48,160
Do I look okay?

439
00:32:48,250 --> 00:32:50,000
-You look perfect.
-You look beautiful.

440
00:32:50,080 --> 00:32:51,830
-Don't worry.
-You're always pretty.

441
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:52,840
I'll put this on here.

442
00:32:52,920 --> 00:32:55,130
Gather together and look at the camera.

443
00:32:55,210 --> 00:32:56,510
Mr. Cha, come closer.

444
00:32:56,590 --> 00:32:58,130
One...

445
00:32:58,470 --> 00:32:59,800
Come closer to each other.

446
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:02,470
-One...
-Is it how it works?

447
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:05,850
Let me see the picture.

448
00:33:05,930 --> 00:33:07,930
I'll show you.

449
00:35:07,470 --> 00:35:10,560
I'm very grateful to Hyeon-jeong.

450
00:35:12,180 --> 00:35:14,230
I'm always grateful to her.

451
00:35:14,730 --> 00:35:16,190
Did you like it, Yu-ri?

452
00:35:16,810 --> 00:35:18,520
Yes. I loved it.

453
00:35:20,190 --> 00:35:22,070
What was so good?

454
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:26,030
I liked the wind,

455
00:35:26,110 --> 00:35:27,570
I liked the air,

456
00:35:27,780 --> 00:35:29,580
and I liked Hyeon-jeong next to me.

457
00:35:30,950 --> 00:35:32,330
I'm glad to hear that.

458
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:36,210
Things will be always like that
from now on.

459
00:35:37,250 --> 00:35:40,290
We will have happy moments
like that every day, Yu-ri.

460
00:35:45,050 --> 00:35:46,180
Do you not want it?

461
00:35:46,970 --> 00:35:48,550
Of course, I want it.

462
00:35:51,930 --> 00:35:53,020
What?

463
00:35:54,890 --> 00:35:56,100
Dad.

464
00:35:56,810 --> 00:35:57,770
Is Dad sleeping already?

465
00:35:58,770 --> 00:36:02,400
Dad, you can't sleep here.

466
00:36:03,230 --> 00:36:05,740
-My gosh.
-It's been less than a minute.

467
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:08,990
It was somewhere around here. Where is it?

468
00:36:09,820 --> 00:36:11,830
There it is. It says Misaeng.

469
00:36:14,580 --> 00:36:17,040
What is he doing here?

470
00:36:20,420 --> 00:36:21,420
Hey.

471
00:36:24,340 --> 00:36:25,670
Gosh, it hurts.

472
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,300
-It hurts.
-What are you doing here?

473
00:36:27,380 --> 00:36:28,930
Gosh, it's not like that.

474
00:36:29,010 --> 00:36:30,140
Let go of me.

475
00:36:30,220 --> 00:36:31,930
-It really hurts.
-Come here.

476
00:36:34,350 --> 00:36:37,230
Come here. I got you.

477
00:36:37,730 --> 00:36:39,940
-Just follow me.
-It hurts.

478
00:36:40,020 --> 00:36:41,270
Hello.

479
00:36:42,110 --> 00:36:44,440
Stay still. Stop.

480
00:36:44,530 --> 00:36:46,940
What's with your arms?

481
00:36:48,150 --> 00:36:49,280
Is something there?

482
00:36:49,360 --> 00:36:51,660
What have you been up to these days?

483
00:36:51,950 --> 00:36:53,620
Why is there a ghost around you?

484
00:36:53,780 --> 00:36:55,330
What? A ghost?

485
00:36:55,410 --> 00:36:56,830
-Stay still.
-Ghost?

486
00:36:56,910 --> 00:36:58,750
I told you to stand still!

487
00:36:58,830 --> 00:36:59,960
Isn't it staying still?

488
00:37:00,540 --> 00:37:02,750
-It hurts.
-Stop it. Stay still.

489
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:12,050
Is he always so stupid like that?

490
00:37:14,060 --> 00:37:15,310
Because she's not here.

491
00:37:16,020 --> 00:37:16,970
Who?

492
00:37:17,310 --> 00:37:18,270
His wife.

493
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:19,600
He's Hyeon-jeong's boy.

494
00:37:19,690 --> 00:37:21,690
Hyeon-jeong. Where are you?

495
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:26,110
Hurry and come right away, Hyeon-jeong.

496
00:37:26,820 --> 00:37:30,610
Gosh, you now know Yu-ri was around you
for five years.

497
00:37:30,700 --> 00:37:32,240
Just come over here.

498
00:37:33,660 --> 00:37:35,870
I didn't know about it.

499
00:37:36,830 --> 00:37:37,870
Are you sure

500
00:37:38,660 --> 00:37:39,870
there's a ghost next to you?

501
00:37:40,750 --> 00:37:43,330
Why? Why is it doing this to me?

502
00:37:43,710 --> 00:37:45,840
Is it because I refused
to write a fake diagnosis?

503
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:48,510
Gosh, it's no big deal.

504
00:37:51,180 --> 00:37:53,680
"Gosh, it's no big deal."

505
00:37:55,640 --> 00:37:56,470
Then why?

506
00:37:57,390 --> 00:37:58,850
Why are you hanging around with him?

507
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:00,850
Right. That one.

508
00:38:00,940 --> 00:38:02,060
There's something

509
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:05,150
only he can do for me.

510
00:38:07,730 --> 00:38:08,940
What?

511
00:38:11,070 --> 00:38:12,700
What is it?

512
00:38:13,070 --> 00:38:15,570
Ms. Mi-dong, please tell me what he says.

513
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:17,080
Why? Why is he doing this to me?

514
00:38:17,160 --> 00:38:20,660
So there's something
only you can do for him.

515
00:38:22,120 --> 00:38:23,250
What is it?

516
00:38:27,550 --> 00:38:29,170
Please tell my mom

517
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:30,970
that I didn't

518
00:38:32,970 --> 00:38:34,090
kill myself.

519
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:41,850
He knows that it wasn't a suicide.

520
00:38:43,100 --> 00:38:45,270
What does he say?

521
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:47,820
What is it? What?

522
00:38:48,690 --> 00:38:50,900
Ms. Mi-dong, please.
I need a simultaneous interpretation.

523
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,900
I can't wait.

524
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:55,570
I'm very anxious.

525
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:27,150
It must've been fun

526
00:39:30,820 --> 00:39:35,820
to see how much I loved her
like some kind of an idiot.

527
00:39:43,250 --> 00:39:45,120
No, it wasn't like that.

528
00:39:47,790 --> 00:39:49,540
Do you know what I said?

529
00:39:52,340 --> 00:39:54,880
I said I'm curious about her
because she looks like Seo-woo's mom.

530
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:58,140
That I'm envious

531
00:39:59,350 --> 00:40:00,970
because she looks like Seo-woo.

532
00:40:03,430 --> 00:40:04,640
I had no idea.

533
00:40:06,770 --> 00:40:08,150
I was like a fool.

534
00:40:21,200 --> 00:40:23,370
You should've told me first.

535
00:40:29,250 --> 00:40:31,090
That's what you should've done.

536
00:40:41,390 --> 00:40:43,600
It has been a while

537
00:40:46,180 --> 00:40:47,850
since you looked so happy

538
00:40:50,270 --> 00:40:52,820
when you were around other people.

539
00:40:56,110 --> 00:40:57,320
I was afraid

540
00:40:59,570 --> 00:41:00,950
you would get hurt.

541
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:10,620
I'm sorry.

542
00:41:21,970 --> 00:41:23,850
Before caring about my happiness,

543
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:27,730
you should care about yours.

544
00:41:29,890 --> 00:41:31,730
Before seeing my wound,

545
00:41:32,230 --> 00:41:34,230
you should take care of yours first.

546
00:41:38,240 --> 00:41:40,150
